                            <comment id="98417" author="yong.fan" created="Wed, 5 Nov 2014 13:44:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is the debug patch:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/12573/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/12573/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="98415" author="yong.fan" created="Wed, 5 Nov 2014 13:31:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;According to the test_logs, the LFSCK status on the MDT4 is &apos;scanning-phase2&apos;, not the expected &quot;completed&quot;. So means the LFSCK on the MDT4 should have moved to the second-stage scanning. Normally, before the second-stage scanning start, the LFSCK assistant thread will generate the LFSCK log &quot;LFSCK assistant phase2 scan start&quot;, but I cannot find such log in the MDT4 debug_log, that is abnormal. The most possible reason is that the LFSCK assistant thread was blocked inside the dt_sync() before generating such LFSCK log message. Currently, we do not know what happened during the dt_sync(). I will make a debug patch to verify that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
